               <p>JOHN M'PHERSON. I <rs id="t18210912-219-viclabel1272" type="occupation">keep a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-219-victim2100 t18210912-219-viclabel1272"></join> in <placeName id="t18210912-219-crimeloc1273">Globe-lane, Mile-end</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-219-crimeloc1273" type="placeName" value="Globe-lane, Mile-end"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-219-crimeloc1273" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-219-off1270 t18210912-219-crimeloc1273"></join>. The prisoner was an occasional customer. On the 26th of August, he came for a pipe of tobacco, I looked through a crevice in the kitchen door and heard the lock of the till go. I ran out, pulled him over the counter, with half-a-crown and sixpence in his hand; he said it was the first time he served me so; I said I thought he had robbed me several times - he acknowledged robbing me six times.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I pulled out 3 s. to see what money I had, the gentleman came and said, "You rascal, you have been robbing the till."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18210912-219-verdict1274" type="verdictDescription">
